# File: tests/features/examples-strategies.feature
#
# Generated from: .claude/specs/feature-add-interaction-strategy-guide-to-examples-command/requirements.md
# Issue: #201

Feature: Interaction Strategy Guide in Examples Command
  As a browser automation engineer starting complex automation work
  I want scenario-based interaction strategy guides in the examples command
  So that I can choose the right approach for common enterprise automation patterns upfront

  Background:
    Given the agentchrome binary is available

  # --- Happy Path: Listing (progressive disclosure) ---

  Scenario: AC1 - List all strategy guides in plain text
    When I run "agentchrome examples strategies"
    Then stdout should contain "iframes"
    And stdout should contain "overlays"
    And stdout should contain "scorm"
    And stdout should contain "drag-and-drop"
    And stdout should contain "shadow-dom"
    And stdout should contain "spa-navigation-waits"
    And stdout should contain "react-controlled-inputs"
    And stdout should contain "debugging-failed-interactions"
    And stdout should contain "authentication-cookie-reuse"
    And stdout should contain "multi-tab-workflows"
    And stdout should not start with "["
    And stdout should not start with "{"
    And stdout should not contain "CURRENT CAPABILITIES"
    And stdout should not contain "RECOMMENDED SEQUENCE"
    And the exit code should be 0

  # --- Happy Path: Detail ("reveal") ---

  Scenario: AC2 - Show individual iframe strategy guide in plain text
    When I run "agentchrome examples strategies iframes"
    Then stdout should contain "iframes"
    And stdout should contain "SCENARIOS"
    And stdout should contain "CURRENT CAPABILITIES"
    And stdout should contain "LIMITATIONS"
    And stdout should contain "WORKAROUNDS"
    And stdout should contain "RECOMMENDED SEQUENCE"
    And stdout should contain "agentchrome"
    And the exit code should be 0

  # --- Top-Level Listing Integration ---

  Scenario: AC3 - Bare examples listing includes a strategies entry
    When I run "agentchrome examples"
    Then stdout should contain "strategies"
    And stdout should contain "connect"
    And stdout should contain "tabs"
    And stdout should contain "navigate"
    And stdout should contain "page"
    And stdout should contain "interact"
    And the exit code should be 0

  # --- JSON Output ---

  Scenario: AC4 - JSON listing is progressive (summaries only)
    When I run "agentchrome examples strategies --json"
    Then stdout should be a valid JSON array
    And the JSON array should have at least 10 entries
    And each JSON entry should have a "name" field
    And each JSON entry should have a "title" field
    And each JSON entry should have a "summary" field
    And no JSON entry should have a "scenarios" field
    And no JSON entry should have a "capabilities" field
    And no JSON entry should have a "limitations" field
    And no JSON entry should have a "workarounds" field
    And no JSON entry should have a "recommended_sequence" field
    And the JSON payload size should be less than 4096 bytes
    And stderr should be empty
    And the exit code should be 0

  Scenario: AC5 - JSON detail returns full strategy body
    When I run "agentchrome examples strategies iframes --json"
    Then stdout should be a valid JSON object
    And the JSON "name" field should be "iframes"
    And the JSON object should have a "title" field
    And the JSON object should have a "summary" field
    And the JSON object should have a "scenarios" field
    And the JSON object should have a "capabilities" field
    And the JSON object should have a "limitations" field
    And the JSON object should have a "workarounds" field
    And the JSON object should have a "recommended_sequence" field
    And the JSON "recommended_sequence" array should have at least 1 entry
    And the exit code should be 0

  Scenario: AC6 - Pretty-printed JSON listing is multi-line
    When I run "agentchrome examples strategies --pretty"
    Then stdout should be a valid JSON array
    And stdout should be multi-line
    And the exit code should be 0

  # --- Error Handling ---

  Scenario: AC7 - Unknown strategy name is an error
    When I run "agentchrome examples strategies nonexistent-strategy"
    Then stderr should contain "Unknown strategy"
    And stderr should contain "nonexistent-strategy"
    And stderr should contain "iframes"
    And stderr should contain "overlays"
    And stdout should be empty
    And the exit code should be 1

  # --- Required Launch Set Coverage ---

  Scenario Outline: AC8 - Required launch strategies are all present with full detail
    When I run "agentchrome examples strategies <name> --json"
    Then stdout should be a valid JSON object
    And the JSON "name" field should be "<name>"
    And the JSON "recommended_sequence" array should have at least 1 entry
    And the exit code should be 0

    Examples:
      | name                            |
      | iframes                         |
      | overlays                        |
      | scorm                           |
      | drag-and-drop                   |
      | shadow-dom                      |
      | spa-navigation-waits            |
      | react-controlled-inputs         |
      | debugging-failed-interactions   |
      | authentication-cookie-reuse     |
      | multi-tab-workflows             |

  # --- Help Documentation (Clap Help Entries steering principle) ---

  Scenario: AC9 - examples --help documents the strategies path
    When I run "agentchrome examples --help"
    Then stdout should contain "strategies"
    And stdout should contain "examples strategies"
    And the exit code should be 0

  # --- Regression Guards (AC11) ---

  Scenario: AC11a - Existing bare examples listing still works
    When I run "agentchrome examples"
    Then stdout should contain "connect"
    And stdout should contain "tabs"
    And stdout should contain "navigate"
    And stdout should contain "page"
    And stdout should contain "js"
    And stdout should contain "console"
    And stdout should contain "network"
    And stdout should contain "interact"
    And stdout should contain "form"
    And stdout should contain "emulate"
    And stdout should contain "perf"
    And stdout should contain "dialog"
    And stdout should contain "config"
    And the exit code should be 0

  Scenario: AC11b - Existing examples <group> still resolves
    When I run "agentchrome examples navigate"
    Then stdout should contain "agentchrome navigate"
    And the output should have at least 3 example commands
    And the exit code should be 0

  Scenario: AC11c - Existing unknown-group error is preserved
    When I run "agentchrome examples nonexistent"
    Then stderr should contain "Unknown command group"
    And the exit code should be 1

  Scenario: AC11d - Existing examples --json shape is preserved
    When I run "agentchrome examples --json"
    Then stdout should be a valid JSON array
    And each JSON entry should have a "command" field
    And each JSON entry should have a "description" field
    And each JSON entry should have an "examples" array
    And the exit code should be 0

  # --- Progressive Disclosure Contract Guard ---

  Scenario: Progressive disclosure is not leaked from listing to detail fields
    When I run "agentchrome examples strategies --json"
    Then stdout should not contain "\"scenarios\""
    And stdout should not contain "\"capabilities\""
    And stdout should not contain "\"limitations\""
    And stdout should not contain "\"workarounds\""
    And stdout should not contain "\"recommended_sequence\""
    And the exit code should be 0

  # --- Cross-Platform Determinism (AC12) ---
  #
  # Note: AC12 asserts byte-identical output across macOS/Linux/Windows. This cannot
  # be verified from a single host in BDD; instead, CI runs this feature on all three
  # platforms and a follow-up check compares the JSON output files. This scenario
  # documents the expectation so CI can snapshot and compare.

  Scenario: AC12 - Strategy listing JSON is deterministic and self-contained
    When I run "agentchrome examples strategies --json"
    Then stdout should be a valid JSON array
    And the output should be deterministic across invocations
    And stderr should be empty
    And the exit code should be 0
